        <div class="cover-mono">Buyer's Guide · AI Blog Writing Tools · 2026</div>
        <div class="cover-title">AI Blog Writing <span style="opacity:0.6">·</span> Tools 2026</div>
        <div class="cover-sub">12 Reviewed · Output quality · On-page SEO · Auto-publish · 90-day window</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="post-body-wrap">
    <div class="post-grid">
      <article class="post-content">
        <p class="lede-p">Most AI blog writing tools draft fine prose and stop there. That is the entire problem. <strong>A blog post is not finished when the words are written</strong> — it is finished when the page is live, schema is in place, internal links point at it, and the image is unique. We tested 12 tools on the full chain and ranked by what actually reaches the live URL.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-tldr">
          <div class="callout-label">TL;DR — Pick by job</div>
          <p><strong>Want publish-ready autopilot?</strong> theStacc — Content SEO $99/mo or Bundle $167/mo. <strong>Want best-in-class optimisation scoring?</strong> Surfer SEO $89/mo. <strong>Want cheapest credible drafts?</strong> Koala AI $9/mo. <strong>Want enterprise brand voice?</strong> Jasper $49/mo. The shortest path from keyword to live URL is theStacc.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>See a finished blog post in 24 hours</h4>
            <p>Get a <strong>free 24-hour demo</strong>. We'll publish a real SEO post to a test site so you can review the content, image, schema, and internal links before you commit.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">Book my free demo <span>&rarr;</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">24-hour delivery · No card</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is an AI blog writing tool?</h2>
        <p>An AI blog writing tool uses large language models to <strong>generate full blog posts from a keyword or brief</strong>. The category covers a wide spectrum:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Drafting tools</strong> — Jasper, Writesonic, Koala AI. Generate text, you handle SEO and publishing.</li>
          <li><strong>SEO writing platforms</strong> — Surfer SEO, Frase, SEO.AI, Scalenut. Score content against SERP competitors.</li>
          <li><strong>Done-for-you publishers</strong> — theStacc, Outrank. Topic plan, drafting, optimisation, image, publish — all included.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">Watch out for these traps</div>
          <p><strong>Trap 1:</strong> "AI-detected" panic-marketing — Google does not penalise AI per se, it penalises low-quality content. <strong>Trap 2:</strong> "Credit" pricing that runs out mid-month on long-form posts. <strong>Trap 3:</strong> Tools that quote a draft price but charge separately for images, schema, and integrations.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested 12 AI blog writing tools</h2>
        <p>We ran each tool across the same niches (SaaS, services, ecommerce) for a 90-day window with the same keyword brief and brand voice samples.</p>

        <div class="stat-grid">
          <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">90</div><div class="stat-lbl">Day Test Window</div><div class="stat-delta">Real sites · live URLs</div></div>
          <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">12</div><div class="stat-lbl">Tools Tested</div><div class="stat-delta">$9 → $149/mo plans</div></div>
          <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">320+</div><div class="stat-lbl">Posts Generated</div><div class="stat-delta">Across all tools</div></div>
          <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">5</div><div class="stat-lbl">Scoring Criteria</div><div class="stat-delta">Output · SEO · publish · price · indexing</div></div>
        </div>

        <p>Scoring: (1) output quality without editing, (2) on-page SEO structure, (3) publishing automation, (4) cost per indexed post, and (5) indexing reliability over the 90-day window.</p>

        <div class="inline-cta dark">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>You do not need 12 trials</h4>
            <p>Skip the 40 hours we spent. <strong>Book a 15-minute walkthrough</strong> of theStacc and see a publish-ready blog post from keyword to live URL.</p>
          </div>
